    <item>
      <title>Part 12: The Standard Library - Don&#39;t Reinvent the Wheel</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/drafts/12-standard-library/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 17 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/drafts/12-standard-library/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Part 12: The Standard Library - Don&amp;rsquo;t Reinvent the Wheel
    &lt;div id=&#34;part-12-the-standard-library---dont-reinvent-the-wheel&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#part-12-the-standard-library---dont-reinvent-the-wheel&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this article, we&amp;rsquo;ll explore Zig&amp;rsquo;s standard library (std). Knowing what&amp;rsquo;s available helps you write better code faster - why reinvent what&amp;rsquo;s already been carefully designed and tested?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Zig standard library is a masterpiece of careful design. It follows these principles:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Explicit over implicit&lt;/strong&gt; - No hidden allocations, no global state&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Composable&lt;/strong&gt; - Small interfaces that work together&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Zero-cost abstractions&lt;/strong&gt; - Comptime evaluation eliminates overhead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-platform&lt;/strong&gt; - Same API everywhere&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;

&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Part 1: Overview - What&amp;rsquo;s in std?
    &lt;div id=&#34;part-1-overview---whats-in-std&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#part-1-overview---whats-in-std&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;The Standard Library Structure
    &lt;div id=&#34;the-standard-library-structure&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#the-standard-library-structure&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    STD ORGANIZATION                          │
│                                                              │
│  std/                                                        │
│  ├── Data Structures                                         │
│  │   ├── ArrayList, ArrayHashMap, HashMap                   │
│  │   ├── LinkedList, SegmentedList, PriorityQueue           │
│  │   └── BitSet, BufMap, BufSet                             │
│  │                                                          │
│  ├── Memory                                                  │
