    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the most fascinating aspects of the Zig programming language is how it compiles itself. Zig is a &lt;strong&gt;self-hosted&lt;/strong&gt; compiler, meaning the Zig compiler is written in Zig. But this creates a chicken-and-egg problem: how do you compile the Zig compiler if you don&amp;rsquo;t have a Zig compiler yet?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Zig Compiler Internals Part 2: The Tokenizer</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/drafts/02-tokenizer/</link>
