    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before the Zig compiler can understand your code, it must first break it down into its smallest meaningful pieces: &lt;strong&gt;tokens&lt;/strong&gt;. This process, called &lt;strong&gt;lexical analysis&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;tokenization&lt;/strong&gt;, is the first step in the compilation pipeline.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Zig Compiler Internals Part 3: Parser and AST</title>
