    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Building trees from tokens with recursive descent&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;

&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Introduction
    &lt;div id=&#34;introduction&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After the tokenizer breaks source code into tokens, the &lt;strong&gt;parser&lt;/strong&gt; organizes those tokens into a hierarchical structure called the &lt;strong&gt;Abstract Syntax Tree (AST)&lt;/strong&gt;. This tree represents the syntactic structure of the program.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
