        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#zig-compiler-internals-part-5-semantic-analysis&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The heart of the compiler: type checking, comptime, and more&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;

&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Introduction
    &lt;div id=&#34;introduction&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sema&lt;/strong&gt; (Semantic Analysis) is the brain of the Zig compiler. While the parser checks that your code is grammatically correct, Sema checks that it actually &lt;em&gt;makes sense&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Zig Compiler Internals Part 6: AIR and Code Generation</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/drafts/06-air-codegen/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 17 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/drafts/06-air-codegen/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Zig Compiler Internals Part 6: AIR and Code Generation
    &lt;div id=&#34;zig-compiler-internals-part-6-air-and-code-generation&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#zig-compiler-internals-part-6-air-and-code-generation&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;From typed IR to machine code (or C, or LLVM)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;

&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Introduction
    &lt;div id=&#34;introduction&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After Sema produces typed &lt;strong&gt;AIR&lt;/strong&gt; (Analyzed Intermediate Representation), we&amp;rsquo;re finally ready for the last step: generating actual executable code. But this isn&amp;rsquo;t as simple as it sounds!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Zig Compiler Internals Part 7: Linking</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/drafts/07-linking/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 17 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/drafts/07-linking/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Zig Compiler Internals Part 7: Linking
    &lt;div id=&#34;zig-compiler-internals-part-7-linking&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#zig-compiler-internals-part-7-linking&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;From object files to executables - the final step&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;

&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Introduction
    &lt;div id=&#34;introduction&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&amp;rsquo;ve written your code, it&amp;rsquo;s been parsed, type-checked, and turned into machine code. But you still don&amp;rsquo;t have a program you can run! The &lt;strong&gt;linker&lt;/strong&gt; is the final piece of the puzzle - it takes all the pieces and combines them into a single executable file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
